## Africana Studies Relation

The Reconstruction Era is a crucial focus within Africana Studies as it highlights the struggle for Black freedom and citizenship in the aftermath of slavery. It underscores the systemic barriers African Americans faced and the resilience they demonstrated in striving for equality, education, and political representation.

